Incogitancy	#452.	 dismiss from the mind, dismiss from the thoughts &c.. indulge in reverie &c. (be inattentive). put away thought
Inattention	#458.	 turn away from, turn one's attention from, turn a deaf ear to, turn one's back upon. abstract oneself, dream, indulge in reverie. escape notice, escape attention
Imagination	#515.	 indulge in reverie. visualize, envision, conjure up a vision
Choice	#609.	 indulge one's fancy. set apart, mark out for
Lenity	#740.	 parcere subjectis [Lat.], give quarter. indulge, allow one to have his own way, spoil. Adj. lenient
Permission	#760.	 accord, vouchsafe, favor, humor, gratify, indulge, stretch a point
Giving	#784.	 accommodate with, indulge with, favor with
Pleasure	#827.	 delight in, rejoice in, indulge in, luxuriate in
Pleasurableness	#829.	 indulge, humor, flatter, tickle
Hope	#858.	 pin one's hope upon, pin one's faith upon &c. (believe). feel hope, entertain hope, harbor hope, indulge hope, cherish hope, feed hope, foster hope, nourish hope, encourage hope, cling to hope, live in hope, &c. n.
Disrespect	#929.	 drag through the mud, point at, indulge in personalities
Selfishness	#943.	 please oneself, indulge oneself, coddle oneself
Intemperance	#954.	 indulge, exceed
